  "summary": "The Gorge Waterfalls ultramarathon is a premier trail running event held in the Columbia River Gorge National Scenic Area, offering runners a grueling yet scenic journey through Oregon's lush temperate rainforests. Competitors navigate technical, moss-covered terrain and significant vertical gain while passing some of the most iconic and powerful waterfalls in the United States.",
  "uniqueFeatures": [
    "The course features a spectacular section where runners pass directly behind the curtain of Ponytail Falls via a natural basalt cavern.",
    "Participants traverse the world-famous Multnomah Falls area, encountering a dense concentration of vertical drops including Wahkeena, Elowah, and Horsetail Falls.",
    "The 100K distance is exceptionally demanding, featuring nearly 12,000 feet of elevation gain across the rugged, historic trails of the Columbia River Gorge."
